Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: apktool extraction fails

Ensure apktool is installed: sudo apt install apktool
Check APK file is not corrupted
Verify sufficient disk space
Issue: Python crypto library errors

Install pycryptodome: pip3 install pycryptodome
Do not mix pycrypto and pycryptodome
Use Python 3.6 or higher
Issue: Pattern scanner finds no results

Verify correct directory path
Check file extensions (.java, .smali, .xml)
Ensure regex patterns are correct
Test with known vulnerable code samples
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated critical vulnerabilities in cryptographic implementations, specifically AES in ECB mode. You learned to identify insecure patterns through static analysis, understand why ECB mode is dangerous through practical demonstrations, and automate vulnerability detection for efficient security assessments.

Key takeaways:

ECB mode reveals patterns and should never be used for sensitive data
Hardcoded keys can be extracted from APK files
Automated scanning improves security assessment efficiency
Always use authenticated encryption modes (GCM) or CBC with proper IVs
Implement Android Keystore for secure key management
Secure alternatives to implement:

AES-GCM (Galois/Counter Mode) - provides encryption and authentication
AES-CBC with random IV - prevents pattern recognition
Android Keystore System - secure key storage
SecureRandom for cryptographic operations
Continue practicing by analyzing real-world applications and contributing to mobile security research.
